This paper is primarily focused on the energy consumption and management of data centres, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the modelling and simulation techniques used to analyze the power consumption of data centres, which could also be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also incorporates environmental parameters such as temperature and humidity, which could be classified under Embedded Systems (cs.ET) and Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
